  "text": "China's economy has been rapidly developing and its population has been consistently increasing over the past 40 years. These developments have led to a continuous increase in energy consumption and a deterioration in environmental quality [CITATION_1] . China has exceeded the United States to become the world's largest energy consumer. However, unlike those developed countries that use clean energy extensively, China remains highly dependent upon traditional energy sources such as coal, oil, and",
